Quiz 50 Layer Masks

Layer mask: selectively ignore Colliders when casting a ray

(Not doing this will cause Jitters with Raycast hits the GameObject)

NOTE: layer mask use the bits in an integer to define which layers are active and inactive

<< : means shift

---

1. How can you ensure that a Raycast only hits objects on the "Hoops" layer?
[Tags & Layers] -> User Layer 12 = Hoops

- var layerMask = 1 << 12;

2. How can you limit the depth of the Raycast to 200 Unity units?

- Physics.Raycast(ray, out hitInfo, 200)

3. By default what is the 'queryTriggerInteraction' parameter set to?

- Use the Global default

4. What is the default 'maxDistance' value of a Raycast if now value is specified?

- Infinity

5. What is the type of a layerMask parameter?

- int